The paper deals with depth estimation from stereo images, which is a common problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method is based on a learning-based framework, which involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and dense connections, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a projection loss, which is a technique commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision. Finally, the paper deals with view synthesis, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and computer graphics.
